The parents of a Peace Corps worker learned Thursday that their son, a volunteer in  Nepal, was safe following and earthquake last weekend that killed at least 750 people in  that country and neighboring India.
Another Peace Corps worker, Bettyjean Bouffard  also called her relatives to say she was safe.
She had been living with a Nepalese family  five miles from the earthquake epicenter.
The Peace Corps has been able to track down  all but three of its volunteers in Nepal.
Monsoon rains and washed-out roads kept them  from reaching some of the volunteers.
There aren't any Peace Corps volunteers in India. 
